<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
When I failed god's (Melkor) quest, he said: 'You failed me, (...) I won't ask you to do such simple task any more' - or something like that. But after few levels, he lost another relic and I got a quest. <p>
<strong><a href="./JulesBean">JulesBean</a></strong>: Good catch, I noticed this a couple of games ago and meant to report it but forgot. As far as I can see from the code, the god will always give keep giving you quests (up to the normal maximum of four), irrespective of you failing some. I don't know if the message should be changed or if the behaviour should be changed... 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./FearofFours">FearofFours</a></strong>: It's the behaviour that is wrong here. I'll take a look at it tonight if I get the chance. 
</p>
